article.description: — Jordan Minor had 15 points as Merrimack beat Central Connecticut 62-46 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Minor leads Merrimack over Central Connecticut 62-46
article.linkText: Minor leads Merrimack over Central Connecticut 62-46
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- — Jordan Minor had 15 points as Merrimack beat Central Connecticut 62-46 on Thursday night. Devin Jensen had 14 points for Merrimack (7-4, 7-4 Northeast Conference). Malik Edmead added 11 points. Greg Outlaw had 13 points for the Blue Devils (4-11, 4-8). Nigel Scantlebury added 13 points. Jamir Reed had six rebounds. Central Connecticut totaled 17 first-half points, a season low for the team. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
